---
import Notebook from '../layouts/Notebook.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config';
---
<Notebook title="about me">
  <p>hi! i'm <strong>{SITE.name}</strong> — a <strong>junior at Boston University</strong>
     studying <strong>Computer Science + Math</strong>, with a minor in
     <strong>History and Linguistics</strong> (🤞 fingers crossed).</p>
  <br />
  <p>i'm a <strong>first-gen student</strong> on the way to grad school, and i'm
     trying to go above and beyond — i'm most interested in where
     <strong>robotics, machine learning, and linguistics</strong> overlap.
     teaching machines to actually understand what people <em>mean</em> is
     basically the dream.</p>
  <br />
  <p>fun fact: i will happily talk your ear off about how literally
     <em>everything</em> is electric and runs on binary at the bottom. it's all
     just zeros and ones in really fancy hats. ✨</p>
  <br />
  <p>how i got here, honestly? my Minecraft was unforgivably bad, and trying to
     fix that snowballed into… all of this. these days i reach for
     <code>C++</code>, <code>C</code>, and <code>Rust</code> before anything else.
     assembly is weirdly fun too — there's a quiet kind of peace in moving bytes
     around by hand.</p>
  <br />
  <p>off the keyboard: a good <strong>dark roast with a hint of vanilla</strong>
     fixes most things. ☕ if you also like coffee, robots, or arguing about
     programming languages — say hi.</p>
  <br />
  <h2>find me</h2>
  <ul>
    {SITE.links.map((l) => <li><a href={l.href}>{l.label}</a></li>)}
    {SITE.emails.map((e) => <li>email: <a href={`mailto:${e}`}>{e}</a></li>)}
  </ul>
</Notebook>
